@node "Overview" "Overview"
@wordwrap
@tab 25
@font "CGTimes.font" 18

@{jcenter}@{u}Overview@{uu}

@{jleft}-This calculator came into being as a learning tool to learn the reaction GUI system on the AmigaOne.  As it was being developed, a little humor was added in, who doesn't like to laugh when they are adding up the money they owe (instead of crying, LOL)!

@{jleft}-The calculator has a square root, percent, and pi function keys.

@{jleft}-The calculator is fully supported by exchange.
@endnode
@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@font "CGTimes.font" 18
@wordwrap
@tab 25

@{jcenter}@{u}Requirements@{uu}

@{jleft}1.) AmigaOne500, AmigaOne X1000 (Os 4.1.1 or better)


@{jcenter}@{b}@{u}Note@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}-Not tested with Micro AmigaOne, AmigaOne SE, AmigaOne XE, Pegasus 2, Amiga 1200/4000 (PPC).  CutRateCalc should work with these systems also.
@endnode
@node "Installation" "Installation"
@font "CGTimes.font" 18
@wordwrap
@tab 25

@{jcenter}@{u}Installation@{uu}

@{jleft}-Simply unpack it anywhere you want.


@{jcenter}@{b}@{u}NOTE@{uu}@{ub}

@{jleft}-It is not recommend that you rename the program's name.  It uses the original name to define the iconify icon.  Also, whatever icon you choose for the program will also be the icon used when it is iconified. If the name of the program is changed, it will default to the Workbench App Icon for use when it is iconified.
@endnode
@node "Usage" "Usage"
@font "CGTimes.font" 18
@wordwrap
@tab 25

@{jcenter}@{u}Usage@{uu}

@{jleft}-CutRateCalc can be started by either double clicking on it's icon or starting it from an AmigaShell (CLI).

@{jleft}-CutRateCalc is fully supported by exchange.  Select CutRateCalc from the list of programs, and then you can choose to Hide Interface, Show Interface, make CutRateCalc Active/Inactive, or Remove CutRateCalc (quit the program).

@{jcenter}@{b}@{u}Gui Control@{ub}@{uu}

@{jleft}-(Gui 0-9) and (Numeric Keypad 0-9) --> Numbers 0 through 9.

@{jleft}-(Gui =) and (Numeric Keypad Enter) and (Keyboard =) --> Equal Operator.

@{jleft}-(Gui /) and (Numeric Keypad /) --> Division Operator.

@{jleft}-(Gui +) and (Numeric Keypad +) --> Addition Operator.

@{jleft}-(Gui -) and (Numeric Keypad -) --> Subtraction Operator.

@{jleft}-(Gui x) and (Numeric Keypad *) --> Multiplication Operator.

@{jleft}-(Gui .) and (Numeric Keypad .) --> Decimal Point.

@{jleft}-(Gui %) --> Percent Operator (Used like 20 "%" 120 "=" 24)

@{jleft}-(Gui Sr) --> Square Root Operator (Used like 20 "Sr" 4.472136)

@{jleft}-(Gui Pi) --> Enters PI 3.141593.

@{jleft}-(Gui CE) and (Menu "Clear Entry") --> Clear Current Entry.

@{jleft}-(Gui CA) and (Menu "Clear All") --> Clear All (Reset The Calculator).

@{jleft}-(Gui <<) --> Copy From Clipboard (NOT IMPLEMENTED YET).

@{jleft}-(Gui >>) --> Copy To Clipboard (NOT IMPLEMENTED YET).
@endnode
